Powered by RubiQube Ad Network Police detectives attached to the Ogun State police Command have arrested a suspected armed robber who robbed a Uber driver in Lagos but was intercepted in Ogun state. Abimbola Oyeyemi, Deputy Superintendent of Police,DSP, who is the Ogun state Police Public Relations Officer told Daily Independent that the suspect one Philip Efosa,29, was arrested with a Toyota Corolla car with Reg. number GUS 15 RU which was snatched at gun point in Lagos. According to him, his arrest followed a message received from the police control room that a Toyota corolla car was snatched by two armed men in Eleko area of Lagos and that the robbers were heading towards Lagos-Ibadan expressway with the said car. Oyeyemi said having received the information, the Divisional Police Officer (DPO) Ibafo Division SP Abiodun Ayinde quickly led his anti-robbery team to the road where they laid ambush for the hoodlums. “About an hour later, the vehicle was sighted by the policemen driving against traffic towards Ibadan road but was blocked by the police team. “The two occupants quickly jumped down and took to their heels but they were chased and one of them managed to escape while one was apprehended by the policemen. “On interrogation, the arrested suspect confessed that they hired the Uber driver to convey them to somewhere on agreed fare but they overpowered the driver and snatched the car from him at gun point. He confessed that they had the intention of taking the stolen vehicle to Ibadan for sale.”Oyeyemi explained. Oyeyemi said the Commissioner of Police, CP, Bashir Makama has directed that the suspect and the exhibit be transferred to the Special Anti-robbery Squad (SARS) for onward transfer to Lagos Command where the vehicle was snatched. The CP therefore appealed to members of the public not to delay in reporting any crime in their area to the Police in order to enable quick response from the police